<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,338]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,342,231,257]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Field notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[350,589,232,257]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Lasiopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="akaishii">
<emphasis box="[350,589,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Lasiopogon akaishii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits upland river beds and streams where it flies among mid stream boulders and banks. The asilids become active at 
<number box="[733,764,272,298]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="80.0">80</number>
°F. They are sympatric with 
<taxonomicName box="[1097,1213,272,297]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Lasiopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rokuroi">
<emphasis box="[1097,1213,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">L. rokuroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and have a similar flight period. See also 
<tableCitation box="[415,501,312,338]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,239,276,300]" captionText="TABLE 1. Summary of seasonality and prey of asilids reported in this paper" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
Table 
<number box="[487,501,312,338]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
</tableCitation>
for prey and seasonality.
</paragraph>
